Description="This App helps manage the NFS server shares and access rights\nThis uses sudo to gain root privilage. So users should be sudoer for the system they use it on. The default configuration points to \"/etc/exports.test\" so should be changed to just \"/etc/exports\"(After you change this remeber to press enter) in the configuration before going live. \n\nUpdated to Check for Tailscale Hosts to be supported, Tailscale is a popular distibuted network. https://tailscale.com\n\n\nThis was tested on opensuse 15.1, Linux mint 19.2-22.3 and Raspbian Buster-trixie Pi 4 so far.\nThis requires that fping, showmount, netstat and nfs-server be installed.\nPlease send problem reports to brian@westwoodsvcs.com\n\nIf your debugging from gambas ide then gambas3 must be started with sudo, and the -c run option should be chosen from the debug parameter menu"
Authors="Westwood"
TabSize=2
Translate=1
Language=en_US
SourcePath=/work
Vendor=WESTWOOD
Packager=1
